  "description": "A flaw was found in the Linux kernel's Open vSwitch component. The flaw occurs when a recursive operation of code push recursively calls into the code block. The OVS module does not validate the stack depth, pushing too many frames and causing a stack overflow. This can lead to a crash or other issues.",
